Export controlled vocabularies list

 

â€ŒThe administrator is able to export the controlled vocabularies list in MS Excel file and use it for a different environment, tenant, etc.

  • A "Download all controlled vocabularies" button is available in the Manage controlled vocabularies page. When selected (1) the list with all controlled vocabularies is exported (2-3);
  • The exported data is stored in an Excel file.

 

  • In the Excel file (1-2-3):
    • all attributes of each controlled vocabulary are exported;
    • all controlled vocabulary values and their attributes are exported;
    • all available translations (languages) for the controlled vocabularies and values are exported;
    • the inactive values also exported with the appropriate flag.
  • The controlled vocabulary values are grouped under the respective controlled vocabulary.
  • The file name is: Controlled-Vocabularies-List.xlsx.
  • The file is in format that can be used for a direct import.
